result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica L Ressler was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 11:13am [mo]
Defendant Jessica L Ressler in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek.   ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Ms. Ressler waives her right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds her over for Trial.

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Joint recommendation of the Parties, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2, #3, and #4.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Ms. Ressler


On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, with conditions:

--to serve 30 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with work-release/Huber privileges to include supervised visits with child, assessments and appointments, to commence on July 3, 2015 at 2:00pm
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--monthly testing for illegal drug use
--to submit DNA sample to designee/ Sheriff upon demand
--to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge
